---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import CompressImage from '../../components/tools/CompressImage';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Compress Image to 100KB Free Online | Filekrush"
  description="Compress any image to exactly 100KB. Runs in your browser — no upload, no signup. Supports JPG, PNG, WebP."
  canonical="/compress/to-100kb"
  heading="Compress Image to 100KB"
  subheading="Reduce any image to 100KB or less — free, private, instant."
>
  <CompressImage client:only="react" defaultTargetKB={100} />

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <section class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
      <h2>Why 100KB?</h2>
      <p>Many online forms and government portals require images under 100KB. Common examples include Indian government services (passport, Aadhaar updates), university application portals, and job application forms that enforce strict upload limits.</p>

      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Drop your image</strong> — supports JPG, PNG, and WebP files.</li>
        <li><strong>Target is pre-set to 100KB</strong> — adjust if needed.</li>
        <li><strong>Download</strong> — your image is compressed to 100KB or less.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Is my file uploaded?</h2>
      <p>No. Everything runs in your browser. Your image never leaves your device. No server, no storage, no tracking.</p>
    </section>
  </Fragment>
</ToolLayout>
